  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0dbb\u0dca\u0db6\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dba \u0db8\u0dd0\u0daf \u0d87\u0db8\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0 LNG \u0d9c\u0ddd\u0dbd\u0dd3\u0dba \u0db1\u0dcf\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dba\u0dcf \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "In the middle of the crisis, America becomes the global leader in LNG",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The United States became the world's largest exporter of liquefied natural gas (LNG) in the first half of 2022, according to the US Energy Information Administration.",
        "Exports increased by 12% in the first six months of 2022 compared to the second half of 2021. This puts the US in a position to beat the other two leading LNG exporters, Australia and Qatar.",
        "Rising natural gas demand and LNG prices as well as global demand are currently high, and since the end of last year, countries on the continent have increased their LNG imports to fill low natural gas storage stocks due to restrictions on imports from Russia.",
        "The EU and Britain increased their LNG imports by 63% in the first half of this year, and more than 70% of US-produced LNG went to the EU and Britain, the agency added."
      ],
